news.title: Navi Mumbai residents fume as open dumpers loaded with construction debris go unchecked
news.para: Earlier, the civic body had issued diktats to stop open vehicles from carrying debris from construction sites and warned of strict action against perpetrators.

news.title: Monitoring panel seeks NCLT direction to implement Suraksha group's resolution plan for Jaypee
news.para: The implementation of Suraksha group's resolution plan would come as a major relief for more than 20,000 homebuyers who have invested in Jaypee Infratech projects.

news.title: SC refuses to interfere with HCs' orders in Indiabulls Housing's case
news.para: Supreme Court on Monday refused to entertain a PIL challenging validity of the Criminal Procedure (Identification) Act, 2022 which allows collection of various biometric measurements of accused, and allowed the petitioner to approach high court.

news.title: Kesoram Industries plans to raise funds from Tata Capital to refinance its Rs 1,500-crore debt
news.para: The company is looking for a one-year finance before the asset moves to UltraTech following regulatory clearances, they said, adding that Kesoram is looking to refinance the debt at 12-13%. Talks for the new loan could close by the end of this month, Kesoram Industries added.

news.title: DTCP demolishes 100 structures in 12 illegal colonies in Gurugram
news.para: The move comes three days after DTCP started surveying colonies across the city to check if any rules have or are being violated. The drives were conducted in 12 illegal colonies.

news.title: Greater Noida: Five years after NCLT's move, 850 RG Luxury Homes' buyers get flats
news.para: Around 850 homebuyers of a condominium in Greater Noida West will get their homes, five years after filing a case at the National Company Law Tribunal when all they could see at the project site were the bare concrete frames of towers.

news.title: Hyderabad: Bhuvanteza Infra projects' director arrested for cheating
news.para: Accused Chekka Venkata Suubrahmanyam, who is the director of Bhuvanteza Infra projects Pvt Ltd, was arrested by CCS sleuths.

news.title: ED freezes Rs 30 crore cash in money laundering case against Supreme Constructions' director
news.para: Builder Lalit Tekchandani collected over Rs 400 crore from more than 1,700 homebuyers in a housing project in Taloja, Navi Mumbai. The project got delayed, and homebuyers were left without flats or refunds. Enforcement Directorate (ED) freezes his assets.

news.title: Repco Home Finance's net profit up 23.13% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Repco Home Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 393.20 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 18.85 per cent from Rs 330.85 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Ashiana Housing posts net profit of Rs 27.80 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Ashiana Housing's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 189.25 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 39.86 per cent from Rs 135.31 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers' net profit dips 2.07% quarter-on-quarter in Q3 FY24
news.para: The company's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 106.14 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 2.35 per cent from Rs 103.70 crore it recorded in the Q2 FY24.

news.title: UP-RERA starts pre-hearing scrutiny of complaints to help homebuyers
news.para: In doing so, UP RERA not only simplified the process of filing of complaints, but made it more comprehensive also, it said in a statement. "Now the process has become more user-friendly and will be conducive to early listing and speedy disposal of complaints.

news.title: Commercial property prices in German drop by 12.1 % in Q4 2023
news.para: For the full year, commercial real estate prices dropped 10.2%, accelerating their decline after small drops of less than one percent in 2022 and 2021, VDP's data showed.

news.title: Bhubaneshwar civic body to collect holding tax from buildings on Idco land
news.para: The civic body was not empowered to collect holding tax from such establishments till the last financial year as buildings that came up on Idco land were getting basic facilities like drains, road and streetlights from Idco.

news.title: Tritax Big Box agrees on possible $1.17 billion offer for UK Commercial Property REIT
news.para: Under the terms of the possible deal, every UKCM owner will get 0.444 new Tritax shares for each share they hold. The companies are poised to have a combined market capitalization of 3.9 billion pounds.

news.title: Arihant Superstructures' net profit declines 21.77% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Arihant Superstructures' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 119.46 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 3.70 per cent from Rs 115.20 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Rajasthan housing department to finalise alignment for Jaipur metro line-II extension
news.para: On Thursday, deputy chief minister and finance minister Diya Kumari in the interim Budget announced extension of the proposed Line 2 of Jaipur Metro from Ambabari to Vidhyadhar Nagar.

news.title: Old Ahmedabad still has highest density of commercial properties
news.para: Spread over 481 sq km, Ahmedabad city has an overall property density of 5,087 units per sq km.

news.title: Greater Noida authority to offer upto 40% rebate on pending dues of builders to revive stalled projects
news.para: The Greater Noida Authority has proposed a one-time settlement scheme offering up to a 40% discount on pending dues of builders. The rebate applies to outstanding dues until March 31, 2023, with a 40% discount for payments made by January 31, 2024.

news.title: Cera Sanitaryware's net profit dips 9.42% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Cera Sanitaryware's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 454.89 crore in Q3 FY24, a dip of 3.42 per cent from Rs 470.99 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
